    "Overall, we conclude that accuracy scores for floods, droughts, and cyclones are consistent across all GPT-4 iterations.",
    "Overall, GPT-3.5 (default model, Fig. 2[a]) seems less reliable than GPT-4, which is the most advanced model.",
    "For instance, GPT-3.5 showed limited abilities to correctly produce responses in accordance with our prompt directions.",
    "As seen in Fig. 2 (b), out of 1,910 prompt requests (i.e., 191 countries × 10 iterations), 38 outputs from GPT-3.5 were in the incorrect format, which did not allow us to further process the outputs.",
    "Note that GPT-4 did not have issues providing the correct format for each of the 1,910 cases, suggesting that it is a more capable and reliable tool than GPT-3.5, at least in this regard."
